author: Lauren Moraski CBS News
title: Naya Rivera and Ryan Dorsey are parents
text:
Naya Rivera has something new to sing about -- the former "Glee" actress has become a first-time mom.
Us Weekly reports that Rivera, 28, and her husband Ryan Dorsey, 32, welcomed a baby boy last month. Although the couple have yet to officially announce the news, a source told the magazine . "They are so excited to be first-time parents. It was a very easy pregnancy and birth."
Rivera announced the pregnancy news in February on her website : "We're having a baby! Ryan and I feel so blessed and can't wait to welcome the newest member of our family."
The new addition comes a little over a year after the couple wed in Cabo San Lucas, Mexico. Prior to that, Rivera was engaged to Big Sean, but they called things off in April 2014. Rivera and Dorsey were friends for years before things turned romantic.
Rivera, meanwhile, is writing a memoir , titled "Sorry Not Sorry: Dreams, Mistakes, and Growing Up," due out next spring.
